<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-04T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-04T06:00:00-05:00" n="506" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221 Dahl, Harold/24: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Seville</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-04T12:00:00+01:00">August 4,
                                1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 4—10:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My August 3 [<hi rend="italic">2</hi>], noon.<note n="88" xml:id="d506fn88">Not printed.</note> General Queipo de Llano stated
                            this morning he would communicate to General Franco the views of the
                            Department concerning Harold Dahl which I conveyed to him orally in
                            accordance with the Department’s July 30, 5 p.m. He hinted that Dahl may
                            be exchanged.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>